abstract: Investors don’t expect the Republican-controlled Senate to remove President Trump from office, according to a survey by RBC Capital Markets.
snippet: Investors don’t expect the Republican-controlled Senate to remove President Trump from office, according to a survey by RBC Capital Markets.

abstract: The British central bank says a supplier, without authorization, provided sound from news conferences ahead of the video feed.
snippet: The British central bank says a supplier, without authorization, provided sound from news conferences ahead of the video feed.
lead_paragraph: LONDON — The Bank of England said Thursday that an audio feed from its news conferences had been released to some investors before it had been made public, giving them a leg up on the rest of the market.

abstract: The candidates must know the quirks of California’s vast political geography.

lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Welcome, Democrats and debate spinners, to the city with a Mexican-American-Jewish-Italian Rhodes Scholar mayor, who is not running for president, in the state with an Irish Catholic governor who surely is, just not this time.

headline_main: Sycophants and ‘General Weirdness’ at SoftBank Vision Fund

abstract: A letter from three former Fox News employees is designed to pressure presidential campaigns to do away with NDAs, calling them “a driving force in silencing workers.”
snippet: A letter from three former Fox News employees is designed to pressure presidential campaigns to do away with NDAs, calling them “a driving force in silencing workers.”
lead_paragraph: A new group founded by three former Fox News employees sent a letter to all presidential campaigns on Wednesday asking them to publicly condemn nondisclosure agreements that deal with workplace environment issues.
